raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "agate" %}
{% set version = "1.6.0" %}
{% set compress_type = "tar.gz" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_val = "1547eb66a4caaea08cc247077e5b3740629be6724a047c94be0ecbbfa52ceb0a" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ compress_type }}
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  number: 3
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip

  run:
    - python
    - six >=1.9.0
    - pytimeparse >=1.1.5
    - parsedatetime >=2.1
    - babel >=2.0
    - isodate >=0.5.4
    - python-slugify >=1.2.1
    - leather >=0.3.2

test:
  imports:
    - agate
    - agate.aggregations
    - agate.computations
    - agate.data_types
    - agate.table
    - agate.tableset

about:
  home: http://agate.readthedocs.org/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license: COPYING
  summary: 'A data analysis library that is optimized for humans instead of machines.'
  doc_url: http://agate.rtfd.org/
  dev_url: http://agate.rtfd.org/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
